com.tibbo.aggregate.common.binding

Interface BindingProvider<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBindingProvider, AbstractDataTableBindingProvider, DataTableBindingProvider

    public interface BindingProvider<T>
    BindingProvider interacts with BindingProcessor by providing available bindings and then reacting to their executions.

      • writeReference

        void writeReference(int method,
                    Binding binding,
                    Reference cause,
                    java.lang.Object value,
                    @Nullable
                    ChangeCache cache,
                    @Nullable
                    Pinpoint pinpoint)
             throws BindingException
        Method is called once a binding was executed, its expression evaluated to some result and the provider needs to write the result into binding target.
        Parameters:
        method - Binding execution method: EvaluationOptions.STARTUP, EvaluationOptions.EVENT or EvaluationOptions.PERIODIC
        binding - The Binding itself
        cause - Execution cause
        value - Value to write to the target
        cache - Change cache
        pinpoint - Origin of the writing
        Throws:
        BindingException - if writing was not successful

      • addReferenceListener

        void addReferenceListener(Reference ref,
                          ReferenceListener<T> listener)
                   throws BindingException
        Method called by the binding processor once the provider should start listening for certain Reference changes.
        Parameters:

        listener - Listener that should be called if the reference was changed
        Throws:
        BindingException - If a listening could not be started
